            means that the relevant transform combination (such as 0 followed \
            by 2) is allowed and if the RIFS flag is disabled then the \
            transform combination is forbidden but you may reverse this state \
            so that an enabled RIFS flag means that the relevant transform \
            combination is forbidden and a disabled one means it is allowed."
